&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/leitourgia/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/leitourgia/> ;
  schema:name "Leitourgia" ;
  schema:description "A Leitourgia is a quadruple (λ, φ, C, ι) — a designated agent in Hohfeldian liability position, a prescribed-form proposition, a witnessing community constituted by the gathering of compatible local witnesses, and a discharge proposition. Full discharge is joint settlement of two predicates: form-enactment (the act has been correctly performed) and forward-stability (the discharge carries forward into all continuations). The personal cost is the irreversible expenditure the leitourgos bears in performing the step that settles the discharge." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-19" ;
